    "body": "This supports the use case where you have some sort of a view (like /usr/local/bin or /opt/rocm/bin or spack environment installs) which contain just symlinks, and you run spack external find with the bin folder in your PATH -- you don't want to have all the unrelated libs as part of your prefix, you just want /actual/path/to/specific/package/prefix to be your prefix.\r\n\r\nCloses #23007\r\nCloses #24452 \r\nCloses #24418",
